reviewText: My daughters can watch these endlessly.  They teach many fun learning and problem solving skills, and introduce children to quality art and music.
Title: Disney Little Einsteins - Flight of the Instrument Fairies

reviewText: What can I say? The Little Einsteins come through again in "Flight of the Instrument Fairies." My son picks up any remotely musical instrument in the house whenever the DVD is on and toots, strums, and bangs away.  I even learn a thing or two about classical music from the Little Einsteins. This was worth the money.

reviewText: Little Einsteins: Flight Of The Instrument Fairies is a 2008 Disney DVD compilation of four episodes of the popular Disney Junior/Baby Einstein Company original series. In this DVD, The Einsteins(Leo, Annie, Quincy, and June)and their Rocket experience four new fairy tale-themed adventures. Such as June is greeted by the Silly Puppets and makes her the Puppet Princess, and the Einsteins help Rocket visit his sick Grandma Rocket and outsmart Rocket's arch nemesis, Big Jet, along the way. The DVD also has Special Features and sneak peeks of other Disney DVD favourites. This L.E. DVD is perfect for little children who like to learn about the Arts and the cultures of the world!
summary: June Is Honoured As The Puppet Princess!

reviewText: My 2 1/2 year old grandson is addicted to Little Einsteins, and of all of them, this was a particular favorite.  He can watch this over and over, ad nauseum... but they are intelligent videos in their own little 'appeal-to-toddler' way, and Disney did a good thing here.  Granted they are very formulaic, but the target audience is munchkin sized.  Definitely a good purchase.
